## CI/CD PIPELINE

For continuous integration and deployment:

1. FOLLOW the GitHub Actions workflow:
   - Build on all target platforms
   - Run tests automatically
   - Deploy to staging environments
   - Release with proper versioning

2. MAINTAIN CI configuration:
   - Keep build matrices up to date
   - Configure caching for faster builds
   - Set appropriate timeouts
   - Report build status

3. AUTOMATE releases:
   - Create GitHub releases
   - Upload build artifacts
   - Generate changelogs
   - Deploy to hosting services

ONE SOLUTION ONLY:
```yaml
# Example GitHub Action workflow
name: Build and Test

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]
  pull_request:
    branches: [ main ]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}
    strategy:
      matrix:
        os: [ubuntu-latest, windows-latest, macos-latest]
        
    steps:
    - uses: actions/checkout@v3
    
    - name: Install Rust
      uses: actions-rs/toolchain@v1
      with:
        profile: minimal
        toolchain: stable
        override: true
    
    - name: Build
      run: cargo build --verbose
      
    - name: Run tests
      run: cargo test --verbose
      
  web-build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
    - uses: actions/checkout@v3
    
    - name: Install Rust
      uses: actions-rs/toolchain@v1
      with:
        profile: minimal
        toolchain: stable
        target: wasm32-unknown-unknown
        override: true
    
    - name: Install Trunk
      run: cargo install trunk
      
    - name: Build Web
      run: trunk build --release
```

